    "_id": "jn764cw67wc4h6d9st0qpe903x83vbgz",
    "createdBy": "kd795pd2q713d3q8q22z5d4a7s822ec0",
    "description": "The hard part of the tool. What happens when the parent is killed? Revocation must be best-effort with a configurable timeout. SIGKILL cannot be caught so rely on TTL expiry as the safety net. Define retry count for failed revocations.",
    "projectId": "9887a770-ff7d-44d4-aeeb-a9c7b2252b73",
    "sourceRefs": [
      {
        "clause": "Missing from original design: signal handling policy identified as the hard part",
        "sourceId": "k177sddehaazcsbdjwzhqwtgw183tkd3"
      },
      {
        "clause": "Audit confirms signal forwarding/process-group/revoke-on-signal policy still open and prioritized in P0 beads",
        "sourceId": "k1716vskd1q7gm1kgfmc9053yh83tfx9"
      }
    ],
    "statement": "noscope shall define and implement a signal handling policy: on SIGTERM/SIGHUP forward signal to child, attempt credential revocation with timeout and retry, log and exit on failure",
