    "_id": "jn77se3zt6bbvvrsw8yakg72e983taj2",
    "createdBy": "kd795pd2q713d3q8q22z5d4a7s822ec0",
    "description": "If TTL is 30m and refresh fails at 25m, the agent still has 5 minutes of valid token. Killing the child on refresh failure is too aggressive. Log, retry, let the token expire naturally if refresh never succeeds. The TTL is the safety net.",
    "projectId": "9887a770-ff7d-44d4-aeeb-a9c7b2252b73",
    "sourceRefs": [
      {
        "clause": "Missing from original design: refresh failure policy not defined",
        "sourceId": "k177sddehaazcsbdjwzhqwtgw183tkd3"
      }
    ],
    "statement": "noscope shall define and implement a refresh failure policy: when token refresh fails before expiry, retry with backoff, and if retries exhausted, log a warning but allow the child to continue with the current token",
    "stats": {
